Section1.Para:
Evaluation of physical characteristics of the films was carried out by an X-ray diffraction (XRD) system (P8 Advan-Bruker) in a scan range of 2θ=20–40∘ with step time of 71.6 s and step size of 0.0342∘. Copper (Cu K
                  α
                ) with wavelength (λ) of 1.5406 nm was used as X-ray source. The top-surface crystallographic properties were evaluated with reflection high-energy electron diffraction (RHEED) using an EFZ4 device at electron energy of 50 keV. Fourier transform infrared (FTIR) (Perkin Elmer Spectrum GX) analysis was performed to analyze functional groups of the films.
